#: includes/modules/TableMaker/TableMaker.php:569
msgid ""
"Here you can set a maximum width for all table columns. For flexible-width "
"columns, it’s recommended to use fraction (fr) units. This can also be set "
"to 'auto'. For fixed-width columns, it’s recommended to use pixel (px) "
"units. This setting can be overridden per column."
msgstr ""

#: includes/modules/TableMaker/TableMaker.php:571
msgid ""
"Here you can set a minimum width for all table columns. It’s recommended to "
"use pixel (px) units. This setting can be overridden per column."
msgstr ""

#: includes/modules/TableMaker/TableMaker.php:573
msgid ""
"Here you can set a maximum height for all table rows. For flexible-height "
"rows, it’s recommended to set this to ‘auto’. For fixed-height rows, it’s "
"recommended to use pixel (px) units."
msgstr ""

#: includes/modules/TableMaker/TableMaker.php:575
msgid ""
"Here you can set a minimum height for all table rows. It’s recommended to "
"use pixel (px) units."
msgstr ""

#: includes/modules/TableMaker/TableMaker.php:579
msgid "Here you can set the number of column headers the table will have."
msgstr ""

#: includes/modules/TableMaker/TableMaker.php:581
msgid "Here you can set the number of column footers the table will have."
msgstr ""

#: includes/modules/TableMaker/TableMaker.php:583
msgid "Here you can set the number of row headers the table will have."
msgstr ""

#: includes/modules/TableMaker/TableMaker.php:585
msgid "Here you can set the number of row footers the table will have."
msgstr ""

#: includes/modules/TableMaker/TableMaker.php:589
msgid ""
"Here you can set the table breakpoint – the point at which the table will "
"display as blocks or accordion."
msgstr ""

#: includes/modules/TableMaker/TableMaker.php:591
msgid ""
"Here you can set whether the table will break by columns or rows. If set to "
"Columns, each column will become a separate block or accordion section. If "
"set to Rows, each row will become a separate block or accordion section."
msgstr ""

#: includes/modules/TableMaker/TableMaker.php:593
msgid ""
"Your table currently has no column headers and will break by rows "
"regardless of the setting above. To break by columns, please add a column "
"header."
msgstr ""

#: includes/modules/TableMaker/TableMaker.php:595
msgid ""
"Your table currently has no row headers and will break by columns "
"regardless of the setting above. To break by rows, please add a row header."
msgstr ""

#: includes/modules/TableMaker/TableMaker.php:597
msgid "Here you can choose whether the table will display as blocks or accordion."
msgstr ""

#: includes/modules/TableMaker/TableMaker.php:599
msgid ""
"Your table currently has no headers and will display as blocks regardless "
"of the setting above. To display as accordion, please add a column or row "
"header."
msgstr ""

#: includes/modules/TableMaker/TableMaker.php:601
msgid "Here you can set the space between each block or accordion section."
msgstr ""

#: includes/modules/TableMaker/TableMaker.php:605
msgid ""
"Here you can choose to enable table scrolling. If set to Off, the table may "
"overflow its containing element. If set to On, any overflow will be hidden "
"and scrollbars will appear."
msgstr ""

#: includes/modules/TableMaker/TableMaker.php:607
msgid ""
"Here you can choose to make column headers sticky. If set to Off, column "
"headers will scroll along with table contents. If set to On, column headers "
"will stick to the top edge of the table, remaining visible."
msgstr ""

#: includes/modules/TableMaker/TableMaker.php:609
msgid ""
"Here you can choose to make row headers sticky. If set to Off, row headers "
"will scroll along with table contents. If set to On, row headers will stick "
"to the left edge of the table, remaining visible."
msgstr ""

#: includes/modules/TableMaker/TableMaker.php:613
msgid ""
"Here you can select the table’s default icon. This setting can be "
"overridden per column or individual icon element. See documentation for "
"details."
msgstr ""

#: includes/modules/TableMaker/TableMaker.php:615
msgid ""
"Here you can set the table’s default icon size. This setting can be "
"overridden per column or individual icon element. See documentation for "
"details."
msgstr ""

#: includes/modules/TableMaker/TableMaker.php:617
msgid ""
"Here you can set the table’s default icon color. This setting can be "
"overridden per column or individual icon element. See documentation for "
"details."
msgstr ""

#: includes/modules/TableMaker/TableMaker.php:621
msgid ""
"Here you can set the table’s default button text. This setting can be "
"overridden per column or individual button element. See documentation for "
"details."
msgstr ""

#: includes/modules/TableMaker/TableMaker.php:623
msgid ""
"Here you can set the table’s default button url. This setting can be "
"overridden per column or individual button element. See documentation for "
