msgstr ""

#: includes/modules/TableMaker/TableMaker.php:625
msgid ""
"Here you can set the table’s default button target. This setting can be "
"overridden per column or individual button element. See documentation for "
"details."
msgstr ""

#: includes/modules/TableMaker/TableMaker.php:627
msgid ""
"Here you can set the table’s default button width. If set to Text Width, "
"buttons will be as wide as their text. If set to Cell Width, buttons will "
"stretch to fill their containing cell. This setting can be overridden per "
"column."
msgstr ""

#: includes/modules/TableMaker/TableMaker.php:631
msgid ""
"Here you can select images to use within table cells. See documentation for "
"details."
msgstr ""

#: includes/modules/TableMaker/TableMaker.php:633
msgid "Here you can set the table’s default image quality or resolution."
msgstr ""

#: includes/modules/TableMaker/TableMaker.php:635
msgid ""
"Here you can set the table’s default image proportion. This setting can be "
"overridden per column."
msgstr ""

#: includes/modules/TableMaker/TableMaker.php:637
msgid ""
"Here you can choose how the table’s images are scaled. If set to Fit, "
"images are scaled to fit their containing cell without cropping. If set to "
"Fill, images are scaled to fill or cover their containing cell. This may "
"result in some cropping. This setting can be overridden per column."
msgstr ""

#: includes/modules/TableMaker/TableMaker.php:639
msgid ""
"Here you can set the table’s default horizontal image alignment. This "
"setting can be overridden per column."
msgstr ""

#: includes/modules/TableMaker/TableMaker.php:641
msgid ""
"Here you can set the table’s default vertical image alignment. This setting "
"can be overridden per column."
msgstr ""

#: includes/modules/TableMaker/TableMaker.php:645
msgid ""
"Here you can set how the table frame or grid will display. If set to Gaps, "
"table cells will be separated by a gap of your choice, allowing background "
"colors and images to show through. If set to Lines, table cells will be "
"separated by a line of your choice."
msgstr ""

